WorldStage Newsonline– Standard Alliance Insurance Plc will be to hold 22nd Annual General Meeting (AGM), the first in the last four year  at the Event Hall, Plot 1, Block 94, Providence Street, Lekki Phase 1, Lekki, Lagos State on 30th September, 2020 at 11am. A notice filed at the Nigerian Stock Exchnage (NSE)  said the AGM will be to receive the audited financial statements for year ended 31 December 2017 and 2018. The notice signed by Kasoki Hart Olekanma, Ag Company Secretary, said the AGM will also be to re-elect Mr Johnson Chukwu as director and ratify appointment of directors It said the register of members and transfer books of the company will be closed from Monday 21st Sept to Friday 25th Sept, 2020.